    },
    {
      "content": "After VMM servers are registered, you can configure cloud protection settings.",
      "pos": [
        12642,
        12720
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you enabled the option <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Synchronize cloud data with the vault<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> when you installed the Provider so all clouds on the VMM server will appear in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Protected Items<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> tab in the vault.",
      "pos": [
        12721,
        12909
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you didn't you can synchronize a specific cloud with Azure Site Recovery in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>General<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab of the cloud properties page in the VMM console.",
      "pos": [
        12910,
        13057
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Published Cloud",
      "pos": [
        13061,
        13076
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        13141,
        13209
      ],
      "content": "On the Quick Start page, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Set up protection for VMM clouds<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        13213,
        13320
      ],
      "content": "On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>VMM Clouds<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab, select the cloud that you want to configure and go to the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Configuration<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> tab."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        13325,
        13355
      ],
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Target<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, select <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>VMM<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        13359,
        13465
      ],
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Target location<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, select the on-site VMM server that manages the cloud you want to use for recovery."
    },
    {
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Target cloud<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, select the target cloud you want to use for failover of virtual machines in the source cloud.",
      "pos": [
        13469,
        13583
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that:",
      "pos": [
        13584,
        13594
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "We recommend that you select a target cloud that meets recovery requirements for the virtual machines you'll protect.",
      "pos": [
        13601,
        13718
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A cloud can only belong to a single cloud pair — either as a primary or a target cloud.",
      "pos": [
        13725,
        13812
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Copy frequency<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> specify how often data should be synchronized between he source and target locations.",
      "pos": [
        13816,
        13923
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that this setting is only relevant when the Hyper-V host is running Windows Server 2012 R2.",
      "pos": [
        13924,
        14020
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For other servers a default setting of five minutes is used.",
      "pos": [
        14021,
        14081
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Additional recovery points<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> specify whether you want to create additional recovery points.The default zero value indicates that only the latest recovery point for a primary virtual machine is stored on a replica host server.",
      "pos": [
        14085,
        14315
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that enabling multiple recovery points requires additional storage for the snapshots that are stored at each recovery point.",
      "pos": [
        14316,
        14445
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "By default, recovery points are created every hour, so that each recovery point contains an hour’s worth of data.",
      "pos": [
        14446,
        14559
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The recovery point value that you assign for the virtual machine in the VMM console should not be less than the value that you assign in the Azure Site Recovery console.",
      "pos": [
        14560,
        14729
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Frequency of application-consistent snapshots<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> specify how often to create application-consistent snapshots.",
      "pos": [
        14733,
        14847
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Hyper-V uses two types of snapshots — a standard snapshot that provides an incremental snapshot of the entire virtual machine, and an application-consistent snapshot that takes a point-in-time snapshot of the application data inside the virtual machine.",
      "pos": [
        14848,
        15101
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Application-consistent snapshots use Volume Shadow Copy Service (VSS) to ensure that applications are in a consistent state when the snapshot is taken.",
      "pos": [
        15102,
        15253
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that if you enable application-consistent snapshots, it will affect the performance of applications running on source virtual machines.",
      "pos": [
        15254,
        15394
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Ensure that the value you set is less than the number of additional recovery points you configure.",
      "pos": [
        15395,
        15493
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Configure protection settings",
      "pos": [
        15501,
        15530
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        15598,
        15705
      ],
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Data transfer compression<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, specify whether replicated data that is transferred should be compressed."
    },
    {
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Authentication<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, specify how traffic is authenticated between the primary and recovery Hyper-V host servers.",
      "pos": [
        15711,
        15825
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Select HTTPS unless you have a working Kerberos environment configured.",
      "pos": [
        15826,
        15897
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure Site Recovery will automatically configure certificates for HTTPS authentication.",
      "pos": [
        15898,
        15985
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "No manual configuration is required.",
      "pos": [
        15986,
        16022
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you do select Kerberos, a Kerberos ticket will be used for mutual authentication of the host servers.",
      "pos": [
        16023,
        16127
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "By default, port 8083 and 8084 (for certificates) will be opened in the Windows Firewall on the Hyper-V host servers.",
      "pos": [
        16128,
        16245
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that this setting is only relevant for Hyper-V host servers running on Windows Server 2012 R2.",
      "pos": [
        16246,
        16345
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Port<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>,modify the port number on which the source and target host computers listen for replication traffic.",
      "pos": [
        16350,
        16462
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, you might modify the setting if you want to apply Quality of Service (QoS) network bandwidth throttling for replication traffic.",
      "pos": [
        16463,
        16604
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Check that the port isn’t used by any other application and that it’s open in the firewall settings.",
      "pos": [
        16605,
        16705
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        16710,
        16864
      ],
      "content": "In <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Replication method<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, specify how the initial replication of data from source to target locations will be handled, before regular replication starts."
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Over network<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—Copying data over the network can be time-consuming and resource-intensive.",
      "pos": [
        16872,
        16964
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "We recommend that you use this option if the cloud contains virtual machines with relatively small virtual hard disks, and if the primary site is connected to the secondary site over a connection with wide bandwidth.",
      "pos": [
        16965,
        17181
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can specify that the copy should start immediately, or select a time.",
      "pos": [
        17182,
        17255
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you use network replication, we recommend that you schedule it during off-peak hours.",
      "pos": [
        17256,
        17344
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Offline<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>—This method specifies that the initial replication will be performed using external media.",
      "pos": [
        17351,
        17453
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It's useful if you want to avoid degradation in network performance, or for geographically remote locations.",
      "pos": [
        17454,
        17562
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To use this method you specify the export location on the source cloud, and the import location on the target cloud.",
      "pos": [
        17563,
        17679
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you enable protection for a virtual machine, the virtual hard disk is copied to the specified export location.",
      "pos": [
        17680,
        17795
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You send it to the target site, and copy it to the import location.",
      "pos": [
        17796,
        17863
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The system copies the imported information to the replica virtual machines.",
      "pos": [
        17864,
        17939
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For a complete list of offline replication prerequisites, see <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a href=\"http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=323469\"&gt;</ph>Step 3: Configure protection settings for VMM clouds<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph> in the Deployment Guide.",
      "pos": [
        17940,
        18139
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        18144,
        18738
      ],
      "content": "Select **Delete Replica Virtual Machine** to specify that the replica virtual machine should be deleted if you stop protecting the virtual machine by selecting the **Delete protection for the virtual machine** option on the Virtual Machines tab of the cloud properties. With this setting enabled, when you disable protection the virtual machine is removed from Azure Site Recovery, the Site Recovery settings for the virtual machine are removed in the VMM console, and the replica is deleted.\n![Configure protection settings](./media/site-recovery-vmm-to-vmm/ASRE2EHVR_CloudSettingsRep.png)",
